article.headline: Albany, N.Y. 55, Duquesne 10
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- David McCarty rushed for 145 yards and two touchdowns and Tim Bush hauled in a 81-yard scoring pass in Albany's dominant 55-10 win over Duquesne on Saturday. Albany built a 41-7 lead in the first half on Vinny Espsito's three touchdowns, two throwing and one rushing. Jon Morgan added a 56-yard fumble recovery. The win was the 16th in a row in the Northeast Conference for the Great Danes (4-2, 3-0). The Dukes' (2-4, 1-2), only touchdown came on a 12-yard pass from Connor Dixon to Jay Spinks, who had 74 yards receiving. Albany's first scoring driving came in a 20 mph headwind. The 80-yard drive was capped by McCarty's first touchdown of 1-yard. Albany added its second touchdown in less than two minutes on Justin Gannon's 78-yard punt return. Albany back-up quarterback Andrew Smith scored on a 58-yard run early in the fourth quarter for Albanys final points.
